\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 No part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 How many rooms were in the house at Kitchener Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Two double bedrooms, a living room - a fair size kitchen and pantry. A yard. With a coal }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15554908\charrsid13503492 house}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  and - dry W.C. in those days. Oh yes. There were no -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 That was outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Outside, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Did your living room have a kitchen range in or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Yes. Every - all the cooking was done on the range in the kitchen. In the living room, yes, it was a kitchen range. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 A sort of living kitchen and a kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Yes. Yes, they were called kitchen and scullery in those days. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 So your living room was really your kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Yes. Yes. You cooked in - it was a living room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 So it was one living room with a range in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 What was in the kitchen then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
Well it was a - what they called in those days was a set pot which you - you - heated your water in for washing. And - a table, which was used and a - a big pantry. And that was all. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 You all had to manage in the one living room then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 There'd be a lot of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Yes, there was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Did anyone else besides your parents and brothers and sisters live in the house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Any relatives or lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15554908\charrsid13503492 Did your mother or father mend or make the family clothes?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Oh yes. That was all - yes, in those
 days - my father did all the mending of shoes. Certain nights for repairing shoes. I could write a book on this. He used to mend all the shoes, he used to cut - cut all the boys\rquote 
 hair. Yes. And my mother used to - my father, for his work, he used to wear 
- navy blue woollen shirts. They had to be wool on account of the hot fire you see and - perspiration you see and she used to make those by hand and he used to have what they called sweat towels which were made out of - linen - white linen that she used t
o buy by - by the yard, and it had to be linen because it absorbed the perspiration. And I can remember this quite well, it used to be a shilling a yard at the stores and she used to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15554908\charrsid13503492 get}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  - a yard and a quarter I think, and she used to cut it down lengthways and then we had to - I had to - hem all round it. I had to sew }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15554908\charrsid13503492 from}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  a very early age. All my father's socks were knitted. So you had to knit, you learnt how to knit as soon as you could}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15554908\charrsid13503492 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  a pair of -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 You used to do it as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Oh yes, as soon as
 you could hold a pair of knitting needles. And - she made all the boys shirts. And - there was an awful lot of renovating done in those days. If an elder child's clothes were anything at all they were cut down for the next ones or if you - in our case we
 had a - my mother had some sisters and they were - there was one in particular that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15554908\charrsid13503492 was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
 in service and she very often was able to send my mother clothes that she got from - the people she worked for. And they were very eagerly looked forward to because - v
ery often were made into dresses for me or in some cases - if they were suits they were - made into trousers for my - we were lucky in those days, we had a - a person who lived next door was a dressmaker. And she used to - and I know she taught me how to 
s
ew and how to make do and mend at a very early age. In those days it was a case of necessity. If you didn't - if you - everything was - everything that had any use in it at all was used to - it had to be, with a family of all those children it had to be. 
And - I - I don't think - it didn't matter how much money I ever had I would never now - I wouldn't be able to be }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15554908\charrsid13503492 extravagant}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
 because - thrift and carefulness was so - and nothing to be wasted; was so ingrained in you and so - lived out in everyday life tha
t it becomes over the years, in fact a part of yourself, that you - not even a crust was wasted. In those days. But the - compared with conditions of today - you can't imagine how - how narrow from a - what would I say - from a - being able to do things w
ith money or - or things, you made use of every little scrap of - thing that you had.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 It's good training for you anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Very good. It's true. Yes. Yes. But - there was a lot of make do and mend both in - in - food and clothing, there had to be.
 Every ha'penny counted. Not even a penny, every ha'penny counted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Did you ever have new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
Yes. I can remember this, my mother was a very - most people were - very staunch members of the Co-op. Yes. It was a kind of a - thrift club to the
m in lots of ways, the Co-op, was a very - was part of your life in those days. And my mother used to run - always run a club with the stores and I can remember she always used to run a club with - and I think it's still going, what they call a Prudent - 
P
rovident - Provident. Yes. You got a card. She used - I can remember this quite well, a man used to come to the house for the money every week, a shilling a week, and for a pounds worth of goods you paid a guinea. You paid a shilling extra a you see. And 
t
hen - you could get a pounds worth of goods and spend them at - so many shops. And I know when my - brothers wanted a suit my mother used to take a club out - and I can remember you could buy a boys suit form a - from a - as cheap as six and eleven for a 
s
uit or two - about eight and eleven. And that would - and I can remember the suits were a jacket and a waistcoat and pair of trousers, and nearly always - if you got anything new, it was at Easter or Whitsuntide. Yes. They were always - that was a - a tim
e when you wore new clothes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15554908\charrsid13503492 
When we were very young we used to have Sunday clothes and weekday clothes, you - your very oldest you wore for school, but - you - in the early days we always had something better for Sundays. There was always - clothes - and s
hoes - for Sundays and you wore them at no other time unless it was a very, very special occasion. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
But - we used to have Sunday clothes and - we used to - there were - I don't think we would have got any - now, my mother and father were very strict. They w
ould never have anything - used to say on tick in those days, they would never have anything on tick. I - although my mother has been very hard up and I know only too well how hard up she was, I can never recollect once either my brothers or I ever going 
t
o a shop without the money. If she hadn't the money we did without it. And that was her very strict rule in our house, we - if you hadn't the money to buy anything, you just didn't have it - apart from this club which used to - you used to get at the stor
es and she used to pay a shillings a week there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 It had to be spent at a Co-op shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
It had to be spent at a Co-op shop. And she used to more or less get - any household things or father's shirts or anything with the - stores club. But this prov
ident club, we used to get our - when we did get them - if we wanted anything new, which was not very often, we used to get them through this - Provident club. I don't think she would ever have - enough ready money to go and buy the new coat or a new - it
 was a - it was bought like that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 And it couldn't be used at other shops, the club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 The Provident club - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 There were two clubs, one at the stores?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 One at the stores and one in the Provident. And there were certain shops, th
ere is one at the end of Nelson Street now, it's just closing, and she used to go there. It's still there. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 So some of your clothes were bought at the Co-op and some at any other shops?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Well - with these Provident clubs there were certain sh
ops you could go and spend them you see. And they - used to buy whatever you wanted and used to put the amount on and that was taken off the thing you see, and that was how we bought - got our clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15554908\charrsid13503492 You don't know the names of any of the other shops where you would have your clothes from apart from the Co-op?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
