\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Did he attend the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Did he bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 No. He was - he was very strict}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2244570\charrsid13503492 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  against gambling. Very, and that was one of the things he - instilled in us. Never to incur any debts. Never get anyt
hing which you can't afford to pay for when you get it. And no gambling of any - any description at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Did your father or mother belong to any savings clubs, such as a boot club, a sick club or a funeral club or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Oh yes. Yes
. You see, in those days, in the early days - there were no insurance against sickness - or even unemployment pay which caused very great hardship. No holidays were paid for. So that - things were very hard when you hadn't a - a - holiday pay. And - most 
people were in sick clubs, my father was in - two or three sick clubs. And - I used to go with him to pay one of these sometimes on a Saturday night. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6503756\charrsid13503492 
I think it was about once a month and it was always paid in a public house which was the Oddfellows, he was in one of them, and - if they were sick they used to get ten shillings a week I can remember and from these clubs. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 And - my father was in either two or three. You had to insure in - in - for hard times or - or be prepared for - for times when you hadn't a
ny pay, people were naturally thrifty in those days. And they were naturally, would I say, they thought about the bad days that were coming when then wouldn't be any pay you see.
\par 
