father. And anything else, occasionally if you went - did any shopping for any of the neighbours, occasionally they would give you a ha'penny and you used to think that was - really good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 You got your pocket money every week did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 On a Saturday dinnertime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 What did you spend the money on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 We never spent a penny altogether, it was always a ha'penny at a time we'd spend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 What did you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Sweets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Did anyone outside the home help your mother to look after her house and family, any relations, friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
Well - the people - the neighbours that she had next door were very good. When mother was ill they used to come and do what they could and - the - the - lady of the house was a dressmaker and she 
used to do quite a bit of - help me mother with her sewing, I mean - if my mother had any garments made she would make dresses for me out of old ones from my mother's sisters or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6503756\charrsid13503492 things like}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  that. And she was very good. And - my mother was good to her in her ways. It was a case of help each other in those days you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Would this be on a regular basis or just when needed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Well I think it was run a more or less a co-operative business, you helped one another in those days. I can remember on baking 
days - my mother always - I always used to have to take a teacake into the person next door. And when they baked they made teacakes and we always got one.;
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 There was more communal living wasn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Oh yes, much more helpful I think they were to other people - to one another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
When your mother was ill or confined to bed the neighbours helped in what way they could, do you remember what happened when any of your younger brothers or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2244570\charrsid13503492 sisters}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  were born, who looked after her then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Well my
 - my mother's sister-in-law, I can remember her coming and staying when - some of my younger ones - but when - from being - eleven year old I got all that. I did it, yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby, you had two uncles in Darlington?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 How much did you see of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
Oh probably once a week, my mother used to go there on a Sunday and my auntie usually used to come at least once a week and have her tea with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 So it was in either of the houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Did your parents have friends that they ever visited?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 No. Just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Yes, and relatives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Did your mother have any friends of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 No. Just neighbours and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Were neighbours ever invited into the home at all, did they ever come by special invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 No, not really, unless you wanted them for some special -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 When they did pop in would they be offered anything to eat or drink?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 When they did pop in would they be offered anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 It was just a case of popping in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 They didn't normally have friends to visit and give them a meal or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 No. Other than the relatives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Did your parents ever go out to visit neighbours at all, or only casually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 I never remember them - going out to a party or anything like that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 It was just relations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 People often tell us that in those days they made their own }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid345345\charrsid13503492 amusements,}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  what do you think your parents did when hey got together with neighbours or relations? Would they make }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid345345\charrsid13503492 music}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  or play games or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
Oh I can remember - going to my mother's brothers wedding when my father - mother went. And they would - have games. Those games - you used to pla
y forfeits in those days, and they used to - everyone would do something, sing or recite or - or - and they would have dancing, I can remember - having dance - clear all the furniture out of the room and sit round and - and have dancing I can remember tha
t
. Not very often. At weddings or - or maybe - this didn't happen in our house because there were - there were too many of us really, there was no room for anything like that. But I can remember it happening at weddings and - New Year evenings you know. Ye
s.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Many people divide society into different social classes or groups, in that time before 1918 did you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid345345\charrsid13503492 think}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  of some people belonging to one and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Oh yes. Very definitely that. I would think that - we used to think - that people w
ho had a sitting room and a living room or a piano or - or - or - a - an extra room, they were better of than we were, and in a different social - scale really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Did you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid345345\charrsid13503492  notice}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  any other different social classes at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Well there were - there wa
s just as much class distinction, probably more, than there is now I would think. Especially where you lived. If your house }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid345345\charrsid13503492 was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
 bigger or if you - or if you had a - clerks in those days were considered to be - a better - a different class because they didn
't soil their hands, they didn't do manual work so they were considered a sort of better class than - than people that had dirty work or - or - things like that. And shop assistants were - thought to be - we thought so because they - they didn't - they di
dn't work in the same }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid345345\charrsid13503492 way}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
 as we - knew that our parents worked and got dirty and - they seemed to have - better conditions. And as I say, where you lived people - in the same way as you distinguish people now. By - by the - clothes they wore and the - it wa
s just - I would say just the same in those days as it is now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Which class would you say you belonged to yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Oh working class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 What sort of people belonged to the same class as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Well more or less the people - the same 
people that lived in your street apart from - maybe one or two that seemed to be better but - working class people were people that had to - work hard for their living. Worked in works and - against shops or offices, they were the kind of people that - di
fferent class, yes. People that worked in offices and shops and things like that. Didn't dirty their hands.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Well - elderly people were always }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid345345\charrsid13503492 treated}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  with respect. And - and kindness. And - they were in a just - a class apart I would think. If anyone - if you were sitting on a chair and - and - and an }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid345345\charrsid13503492 
elderly}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  person, or even anyone - a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid345345\charrsid13503492 grown}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
 up came, you - you knew without being told you had to get up and let the people sit. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Were you ever told to curtsey or show respect in some way to anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 No, not in that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Was there anyone you called sir or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 I cannot remember. Except the schoolmaster and schoolmistress. Yes. They were always called sir and madam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in these ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6503756\charrsid13503492 In the part of Darlington where you lived, who were considered the most important people?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Shopkeepers. 
Your bosses at work. Doctors and all the ministers and - people that employed people. People that got on a council. Or on the - any people that had any authority at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Did you ever come into contact with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Not intimate contact, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Why do you think these people were considered important, because they had authority did you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
Well they had - they had power these people you see. I can remember my father talking about his boss and - and - and things like that and - they - they tal
ked about them, well, I would think they were - had to respect them because they - they held their livelihood in their hands really and - and unless they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824000\charrsid13503492 treat}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  them in the proper way and with respect and - that they thought their - job demanded then your job}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824000\charrsid13503492  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 was in their hands so it was a matter of - of necessity in those days I would think. You had to tre}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824000\charrsid13503492 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 t any employers with respect and - and - some people - some impose this more than others but I would think the majority - there was that distinction betw
een an employer and an employee, a great distinction between the two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Why would you think particularly the shopkeepers were considered important, for the same sort of reason?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Yes, I think so. You thought - I don't know why but you always thought
 shopkeepers were people who would have plenty of money you see. You didn't go into the whys and means of why they had these things to sell, you just assumed that they had a lot of money because they had these things to sell.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Who do you think the shopkeepers associated with, who did they have for friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
Oh I - I think they - they had their own - shopkeepers - friendly with shopkeepers and - I think people did keep into their own class, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 And the clergy, who do you think they would associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
Oh well - there again I think people with the higher positions in church. And we were the - we were conscious of being - the poor relations always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Who would the teachers associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Well I - as far as I could remember I would think they would associate with them - more or less with themselves.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Did you ever come across any farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 And the employers, who would they associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 With themselves I think. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824000\charrsid13503492 Looking back I think people were more clanni
sh than they are now. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Much more clannish because - there was more risks involved really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 What sort of people would you say went to church, any particular type?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 No, because - I would think they were a cross section myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 And chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
I - I think they were more people - definitely more people went to chapel in those day, far more people than do now because - if you wanted any social - if you wanted social life in a family - you connected with the chapel because you - you your enjoyment
 came from there, it wasn't only chapel on a Sunday, it was the things they had during the week you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Would you say the same sort of people went to church as went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Well I have no experience of church. I - we've always been to chapel 
you see and - I have no experience of church people much. Not in - not in those days of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 You say the chapel people were a cross section really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Yes. Yes, I would say so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Where you lived did all the people in the working class have th
e same standard of living or would you say there were different groups even within the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
Oh yes, there were different groups I think, because of course - some people had very big families and the standard of living there was much lower t
han people that hadn't many children, although they were on the same job as those that - there was a standard set by the very numbers there were in the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 So the standard of living of families in the working class depended on the number in the family?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
Yes, and it also depended to a great extent - in - in those days there was a - looking back, there was a lot of people who drank heavily in those days. And - I can remember one or two in our street that used to. And - consequently their standa
rd of living was lower because they used to spend far too much on drink, and things like that. And - then - then that used to lower the standard. And families used to lower the standard you see, in a street you would get a - you would get a - a different 
s
tandard of living among the people in the same street, just by force of - circumstances, either in the family or in the way they spent their money. Well for instance, the family next door, he was a painter. And - he used to - like drink, far too much. Con
s
equently if he got hold of any money he used to spend it on drink. Well that meant that his family - his - his wife used to take in sewing. And in those days - it was more renovations than new things, it was sort of - old things made out of - new things m
a
de out of old things which meant a lot of unpicking and really hard work. And painters in those days were - had a lot of - off work in the wintertime when they couldn't work you see. And - he used to go away and - for weeks on an end - painting in schools
 and things like that just to keep going in the winter. Sell of course if - his wife hardly }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid345345\charrsid13503492 got}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
 anything of him because - when he was away from home all his }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid345345\charrsid13503492 money}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  went on drink you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid345345\charrsid13503492 And}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  - that made a difference in the standard of living you see. And the
n I can remember another - another one that used to drink and - and then you got people that - I just know this by what's been said by me mother and other people that - they didn't know how to spend their money correctly, the same as they do now you see. 
If you give two people the same money, they - they'll - they'll spend it in different ways. And there were feckless people in those days that didn't know how to spend their money wisely, just the same as they are now. So that in one }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid345345\charrsid13503492 street}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  you could get qui
te a - and they're all probably earning - more or less the same wage, because wages were very static in those days, I mean they didn't fluctuate like they do now. Prices stayed the same for years you know. So that really it was how you spent your money an
d - how many in family there were. That made you have a certain standard of living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Do you think that one group felt itself superior to the rest, one group in the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Well looking back we always felt that there were certain people in o
ur street that - that thought themselves above everyone else, and I suppose the same thing happened in all of the - all of the class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Why do you think they thought themselves superior?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Well they didn't mix like some people you see. I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824000\charrsid13503492 didn\rquote t}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  know why you can describe it but they were just distant. They kept themselves very much to themselves and - and their children didn't come and play with you like - the ordinary and you - you 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824000\charrsid13503492 know}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  - you knew it, although you were children you knew - you sensed that. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Were some families thought of as rough and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Oh yes, I would think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Do you remember a distinction of this kind between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Oh I would think there was great distinctions in - and
 I just know this by hearing my father talk between craftsmen and - and labourers. There were - people had a lot of pride in those days and whether it was foolish pride I don't know but there was distinctions in - in between - between craftsmen and labour
ers and my father thought he was much better than his labourers, I mean you got that distinction, you - your father - oh - because your father was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15554908\charrsid13503492 furnace man}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  and someone had to bring his coal and things like that that he felt him - he was better than - the man - well, in fact, they used to call - I think they used to call the man that whe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824000\charrsid13503492 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 led the coal the donkeyman, so that's obvious - the distinction you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Well I - I - I don't know how to answer that. They were conscious of - of class distinctions just like everyone was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Did they have the same attitude to people, how did they treat - people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Well I - I really couldn't say, but I 
know they were conscious of class distinction because - they were very conscious that they had a big family and that - that put them in a class outside - certain people You were more or less - looked down upon really if you had a big family and that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid345345\charrsid13503492  social}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Oh working class. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Why do you think that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Well that's what they were, they never had any - material }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid345345\charrsid13503492 means}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  to get out of - circumstances forced them int
o that - particular class. There was no question of them - ever getting out of it with the - with the family they had and the way my father used to work and the - off times he used to have, there was no chance of them ever being anything else but working 
class people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Could she have thought this because she was thinking of her house or your father or her parents or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 I don't think she would think anything about it. I think you just - you just accepted your life and you couldn't get out of it 
and that was it, I don't think there was any - thoughts about it all as far as I can remember.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another and can you remember anyone who did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 I can't because - jobs were so scarce. They were terribly }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824000\charrsid13503492 scarce}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  all the time I was a child. You wouldn't dare to move from one job to another. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824000\charrsid13503492 
Because you might have lost it you see, you would never be - in my - in my experience anyway, there were very few people that changed jobs, unless it was forced on them by being redundant or out of work. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 There were very few people that would give up a job to - to try and better themselves because - insecurity was such a great thing in those days. I mean, if you got a secure job well you thought that was oh somethi
ng to - that was - that was it, if you had a secure job you see. There were so many people that were - lived from hand to mouth with just a job for a few weeks and then looking round for another one you see, that - if you had a regular job you - you would
 be content with that you see, you wouldn't - I wouldn't think you would dare - try for anything else in case you lost - it wasn't secure. That's in my experience anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Do you remember anyone being described as a real lady or a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Oh many times I can -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Why do you think that was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
By the quality of their lives I think, by the character. Character was a very you judged people in those days by their character and their kindness and they way they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824000\charrsid13503492 treat}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  you and - of many people I've heard my father and mother say, oh - he was a real gent. Or - she was a real lady. And looking back it was the quality of their lives and the way they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824000\charrsid13503492 treat}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  - they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824000\charrsid13503492 treat}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  people, that gave them that - that gave them that - title.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824000\charrsid13503492 Oh many, many times, we were frightened of policemen. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Yes. Yes. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824000\charrsid13503492 We used to tell one another when the - a policeman were coming, especially if we were making a noise or we were playing football or - or cricket and}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13503492  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824000\charrsid13503492 because even in those days you weren't supposed to play cricket in the streets you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
But we used to in the back lanes and - and you used - in fact we used to set somebody to watch for when the policeman was coming just to tell us when t
he policeman was on his way, you see, oh yes. It was rather a sport really to - tell one another you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 When you were naughty did your mother ever say, I'll call a policeman?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Oh many times, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 How did you think the policeman treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Well there used to be a lot of policeman lived in our street }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824000\charrsid13503492 as a}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  matter of fact. But - we were afraid of them, we were very - conscious of their - the - the - policeman's jobs. Very conscious of it. And - oh if a policeman went to so
meone's door we thought that was a tragedy you know, everybody wondered what he'd gone for and - and who was in trouble or things like that you know. 'Cos in those days there people - there were policeman on the beat you see, and they had to go up and dow
n streets and - things like that. They were far more in evidence than they are now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Did you ever notice how he treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Policemen? Well he was always very stern in his speech when he was talk - I mean, if - they used to - you know - sa
y, now, if he saw you playing cricket - now clear off, now go on. You obeyed them }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid345345\charrsid13503492 instantly}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
 you see because you knew they were the law and - and - that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Did you see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Every - every Monday he used to come for the rent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 What did you feel about him as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
He was a nice landlord. Do you want the rent, I can tell you - do you want how much the rent? Oh yes. Our - the landlord of our house built them. He built quite a lot of streets round where we lived and they called his name Thornton, in there's a }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824000\charrsid13503492 Thornton}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
 Street in Darlington, named after this man. And I can remember my mother saying - they lived in this one house all their married life, they went there when the
y were married and I can remember my mother saying that if they could have bought it, anyone had bought them, they would have bought it for a hundred and twenty pounds. The rent was four and tuppence a week. Until the first - just before the first world w
a
r. It was four and tuppence a week and that included the rates and the water rate. And he used to come every week for the rent. But he never used to get it when it was my father's holiday. We always used to - we had to miss the rent that week you see. And
 then you used to pay - my mother used to pay - tuppence or threepence a week off the arrears and by the next weeks holiday it was just about square again, things like that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 He was quite agreeable to you doing that was he?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Yes. Yes. He -
 he knew. He also knew that my mother - never - let her rent go. And he - we used - another thing I can remember, we paid four and tuppence a week rent and - up 'til before the first world war he used to have a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid345345\charrsid13503492 builder\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  yard at the bottom of the street - and he used to get enough paper }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid345345\charrsid13503492 to}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  paper one room every year free. Yes. Used to go and choose. Never good choice of paper but you could. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Do you remember feeling that your parents had a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 How did you feel about that yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Very frustrated at times. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824000\charrsid13503492 Very, very frustrated. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Very frustrated.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 What difference did it make to the family when your father was ill or out of work, was he ever ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Yes, he had - his job you see, he used to - get b
ronchial trouble. And I can remember he was off with pneumonia for about - oh - over a month. That was very hard times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 How would you manage then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Well he had these three sick clubs you see. And I can remember when he'd been off a month, his - one his }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid345345\charrsid13503492 workmen,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
 they had a collection in the works and I can remember him bringing my mother - either two or three - two or three pounds, something like that, the men had collected and sent you see. Things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Everybody helped everybody else didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
Oh yes. Yes. It was very - hard in the early days because there were - there was no - insurance in those days, I don't think insurance came in until after 1911.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 How often he was he ill, do you remember, or off work at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Well he never stayed off work unless}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824000\charrsid13503492  he was abso}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
lutely ill and as I say I he had - I can remember him having influenza once or twice and I can also remember him having been off this about - oh - maybe up to six weeks with pneumonia. And that was all that I ever
 remember. But was - we used to dread it, my mother used to dread it because - it was very difficult to manage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Was he ever actually out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Oh yes. Yes. Yes. He was out of work because in the winter there used to be difficulty in getting c
oal. If it was bad weather they couldn't move coal about, which was very essential to his job. And another thing, he often used to have a day or two off because he had a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824000\charrsid13503492 forge man}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  that used to be a very heavy drinker and he used to go on the booze and then
 he would lay the whole - hammer off you see, so that was another dreaded thing in our house. And - as I say - holidays, there was no pay and - sickness, especially with my father was dreaded because that meant a lean time and a lot of - scraping and - im
provisation and making do and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Did you ever get any help from the guardians or the parish or any charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
Yes. I can remember - it would be either during or just after the war or just before, but I can remember. My father was out of work - or m
aybe it was a strike or something, occasionally there were strikes in those days. And there were no reserves of money ever in your house. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824000\charrsid13503492 
If my father was off a week - he would work a week and in those days they always used to keep a week's pay in hand. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 So if my father had been off a week, say through this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824000\charrsid13503492 forge man}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
 or - or anything happening, or even that - he would work a week and then he would have what he called a sub off his wages you see. And he would get maybe a pound sub and that would have to do - 
for that week. But that was taken out of the - out of the next weeks wages you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824000\charrsid13503492 And it meant you had - for two or three weeks you had not quite a week\rquote 
s wages, you had maybe half or threequarters of a week's wages you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 And that's what he had to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 How often would he really be out of work apart from illness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
Oh - he would have - oh I think - I can't remember exactly, but I know he had - periods when there was a strike and I can remember him - it would be after the - first - just after the
 first world war when a depression came and there was a lot of out of work, and there was no unemployment benefit, and he had to go what was called the - guardians in those days, and I can remember he didn't get money. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2824000\charrsid13503492 He got a voucher that he had to take - he got so much money and it wasn't much, and he had a voucher that me mother had to take and spend at a certain grocer's shop on groceries. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Not money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 How did the guardians treat you, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 My father hated to go and he would - he wo
uld - have to be really desperate. I can only remember - oh, two or three occasions. It was against his - he was a very proud man although he was a - he had nothing in the way of material things to be proud of but he - he was - and it was a - quite agains
t his nature and his grain to go and ask for anything. But it - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824000\charrsid13503492 circumstances}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
 made him and I can remember he - he brought this for mother}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid345345\charrsid13503492 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  a voucher for groceries that she had to go for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 How did you feel about having help from the Guardians?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Oh 
bad, bitterly, because my father - it was really the same feeling in us you see. And we felt it was degrading in some way. It's - it - it wasn't a good thing at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 But how would you say the guardians treated you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824000\charrsid13503492 Oh very, very - according to standards now it - it was dreadful really. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
It wouldn't buy the bare necessities of - life, what they allowed you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 When there was someone in the district whom the people disapproved of very strongly was there any special way in which they showed it
, do you remember anyone being made to leave by what they called rough music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 No. No. No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Were you given lessons by your parents or a tutor or a governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Privately you mean? No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Between four and five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 When you first started what time in the morning did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 When did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Four. And then it got to half past three. I can remember }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824000\charrsid13503492 changing}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  from - yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 So you started to do a full day straight away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824000\charrsid13503492 What kind}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  of a school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Oh I liked school, it was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Was it an elementary school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Oh yes, it was an elementary school. And it was - in the district and you - you - I started at that school and
 finished at that school. You didn't change schools at all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Was it for boys and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid345345\charrsid13503492 Boys}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
 and girls, but there was a - they were mixed in the infants, in the primary, we called it the infants. In those days we called the young school the infa
nts and then you got into the big boys and big girls. That was what we called them you see. There was no juniors in those days, you went from the infants to the big girls or the big boys, that was what we called it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 What school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Corporation Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Walked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 How long did it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Oh - five minutes. And less if you were in a hurry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Who went with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Oh just our friends, my brother or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Where did you have your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Home. There weren't any school meals in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 I loved it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Well we had our }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid345345\charrsid13503492 favourite}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Did you like them on the whole or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Oh - there were some we liked and some we didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
Did the teachers emphasise certain things as important in life, such as manners, tidiness, punctuality or - ways of speaking, U think you said you were caned if you were late?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Oh - oh yes, the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824000\charrsid13503492 discipline}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  was v
ery strict. Yes. Yes. We had had to have clean shoes and clean hands, in fact there used to be inspections sometimes. The headmistress would have - the headmistress, when you got into the big school, would have an inspection for hands and - and your shoes
 cleaned and things - and your neck and things like that. And she would send you to wash them if they weren't clean. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Were they keen on manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Well just please and thank you, which - manners were always - important in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 You said you were caned if you were late?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
Certain times, yes. If - if - periodically she would stand in the yard and - all late comers would be lined up and then you got a - a cane, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Did they emphasise ways of speaking as important at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 No, not really, but we did have - looking back we had quite a lot of reading aloud at school and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2824000\charrsid13503492 poetry}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  and things like that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen, you mentioned the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Oh yes, we were caned, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Did the girls get the same punishment as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 As far as I know yes, I know the headmaster was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid345345\charrsid13503492 very}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492  strict disciplinarian and he caned - you just accepted it, if you done wrong you got the cane and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 For what sort of offences, you mentioned being late, any other offences that you'd get the cane for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2824000\charrsid13503492 
Well - well if you were disobedient in class, if you were talking - when you should have been attentive in a class and you weren't listening and things like that.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Oh yes, you told them -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9001745 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 They asked what you did at school did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8342232 EE  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14499774\charrsid13503492 Oh yes. Yes.
